timing_resolve_driver_conflicts(25.10)  timing_resolve_driver_conflicts(25.10)

Name
       timing_resolve_driver_conflicts

Syntax
        timing_resolve_driver_conflicts

       {conservative | aggressive}

       Default: aggressive

       Resolves constant propagation results on nets with multiple drivers.

       When set to conservative mode, the net values are as follows:

              * If all the drivers are 1, the net will be driven to value 1

              * If all the drivers are 0, the net will be driven to value 0

              * In other cases, the net value will be Undefined

       When set to aggressive mode, the net values are as follows:

              * If some of the drivers are 0, the net value will be 0

              * If  some  of  the  drivers are 1, but none are 0, then the net
                value will be 1

              * In other cases, the net value will be Undefined

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

